{"title_page": "List of books from the Richard & Judy Book Club", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n[[File:Richard and Judy Book Club, W.H. Smith, Enfield.jpg|thumb|Richard and Judy Book Club display at W.H. Smith, Enfield.]]\nThe following is a list of books from the [[Richard & Judy]] Book Club, featured on the television chat show. The show was cancelled in 2009, but since 2010 the lists have been continued by the Richard and Judy Book Club, a website run in conjunction with retailer [[W H Smith]].\n\n==Main list==\n'''2004'''\n*[[Monica Ali]] \u2013 ''[[Brick Lane (novel)|Brick Lane]]''\n*[[Martina Cole]] \u2013 ''The Know''\n*[[William Dalrymple (historian)|William Dalrymple]] \u2013 ''[[White Mughals]]''\n*[[Zo\u00eb Heller]] \u2013 ''[[Notes on a Scandal]]''\n*[[David Nicholls (writer)|David Nicholls]]  \u2013 ''[[Starter for Ten (novel)|Starter for Ten]]''\n*[[Joseph O'Connor]] \u2013 ''[[Star of the Sea]]''\n*[[Alice Sebold]] \u2013 ''[[The Lovely Bones]]'' (''winner'')\n*[[\u00c5sne Seierstad]] \u2013 ''[[The Bookseller of Kabul]]''\n*[[Nigel Slater]] \u2013 ''Toast: The Story of a Boy's Hunger''\n*[[Adriana Trigiani]] \u2013 ''[[Luc\u00eda, Luc\u00eda]]''\n\n'''2005'''\n*[[William Brodrick (writer)|William Brodrick]] \u2013 ''The Sixth Lamentation''\n*[[Paula Byrne]] \u2013 ''Perdita: The Life of Mary Robinson''\n*[[Justin Cartwright]] \u2013 ''The Promise of Happiness''\n*[[Karen Joy Fowler]] \u2013 ''[[The Jane Austen Book Club]]''\n*[[Chris Heath]] \u2013 ''Feel: Robbie Williams''\n*[[David Mitchell (author)|David Mitchell]] \u2013 ''[[Cloud Atlas (novel)|Cloud Atlas]]'' (''winner'')\n*[[Audrey Niffenegger]] \u2013 ''[[The Time Traveler's Wife]]''\n*[[Jodi Picoult]] \u2013 ''[[My Sister's Keeper (novel)|My Sister's Keeper]]''\n*[[Andrew Taylor (author)|Andrew Taylor]] \u2013 ''The American Boy''\n*[[Carlos Ruiz Zaf\u00f3n]] \u2013 ''[[The Shadow of the Wind]]''\n\n'''2006'''\n* [[Julian Barnes]] \u2013 ''[[Arthur & George]]''\n